node.text:
This Asian Pacific Islander Heritage Month, our API community is sharing how their heritage inspires their creativity. Hear @the.korean.vegan’s powerful reflections on her grandmother and share your work with the hashtag #OurDearElders for a chance to be featured.

"I’ve partnered with @adobe to honor #OurDearElders, and today, I honor my grandmother. My brave, ferocious, loving grandmother. Who slipped out of North Korea through swamp water and cut through the mountains on foot, all while keeping my father safe. Tell me, how do you honor your elders? How have their stories shaped you? What are some of the foods you like to eat in remembrance of those who came before you? Share how you honor them with #OurDearElders so that we can all join in on this beautiful discussion." - Joanne Molinaro

node.text:
September Affirmation: "I intend to feel fulfilled in my life. I am deserving of joy, healing, and self-liberation." 🍃

In this week's #WomenCreateWednesday, discover how author @alex_elle explores affirmations, gentle reminders, and the truths of life through literature and language.

node.accessibility_caption:
Text graphic in black and white text that reads: 
"Gentle reminder:
When something isn't meant for you, forcing it won't make it more for you. Release the urge to force things to fit into your life. What is meant for you won't miss you - believe that." - Alex Elle

Photo of this week's feature, Alex Elle. Her photo is in an arched frame with a white and orange background behind her. Her hair is in braids with Monarch butterfly clips in it, and her black tank top reveals her colorful tattoo sleeve on one arm. The text on the image says "Featuring Alex Elle" in a vibrant pink color, and a circular red "Women Create Wednesday" logo is in the top right corner.
Photograph of Alex sitting on a floor surrounded by colorful abstract art pieces.
Graphic of a text quote: "Tell your story - no matter what. Be true to your craft and don't forget how valuable you and your art are." - Alex Elle, Writer
